			<h3 class="about-page-subtitle">Overview</h3>
			<p>
				The MIT Regional Entrepreneurship Acceleration Program (REAP) is an innovative two-year program designed to work with regional teams around the world to enhance and accelerate their entrepreneurial ecosystem.  With a focus on prosperity and on enhancing both general regional strengths and specific areas of industry, MIT REAP enables regional teams to develop and implement a custom acceleration strategy to propel their region’s economic growth through innovation-driven entrepreneurship (IDE).
			</p>
			<p>
				Our approach is multi-stakeholder in nature. MIT REAP brings together diverse teams from the government, entrepreneurial community, large corporations, universities and risk capital to develop and share global best practices.  MIT REAP is an opportunity for regions to both build bridges internally across stakeholder groups in your region, and to exchange ideas externally with other member regions. 
			</p>
