			<h3 class="about-page-subtitle">Results</h3>
			<p>
				MIT REAP implements the Institute’s expertise in entrepreneurial ecosystem development. Partner regions accelerate their growth by engaging in the two-year non-degree program. MIT REAP opens by identifying regional challenges to economic growth. Partner regions subsequently develop and implement a custom REAP strategy informed by MIT frameworks. A REAP cohort is composed of eight international partner regions. One of the greatest strengths of the MIT REAP experience is inter-regional collaboration. International collaboration between partner regions aligns regional strategies with global best practice. MIT REAP teaches partner regions how to use accelerators, prizes, diaspora and risk capital to catalyze regional economic growth. 
			</p>
			<p>
				Partner regions measure their regional performance by using the data-driven REAP dashboard. The dashboard is composed of region-specific metrics associated with IDE ecosystem development. The REAP Dashboard allows partner regions to learn from each other, fostering international relationships that extend beyond the duration of the program. After the two-year cohort closes, partner regions continue progress on the projects initiated during REAP with guidance from MIT faculty.
